Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the
@Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things
milder), season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a
single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain the @halloumi{225%g} and slice into 1cm wide batons for your
halloumi fries. Place into a small #bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin
strips. Set aside for now.

Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the
flesh out onto a board. Cut into 1cm chunks and pop into a medium bowl.

Quarter the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g} and add to the bowl of avocado.

Cut the @lime{1} into wedges.

Drizzle some @olive oil{} over the avocado and tomato salsa, squeeze in some
lime juice, then season with salt and pepper. Mix together and set aside.

When the potato fries are halfway through cooking, remove from the oven. Add
the sliced pepper to the same #baking tray{}, drizzle with a little more oil
and toss together. Spread out in a single layer.

Pop back into the oven to bake for the remaining time, ~{12-15%minutes}.

In a medium bowl, combine the @coleslaw mix{120%g} with half the
@soured cream{150%g}. Season with salt, pepper and a squeeze of lime juice
from a lime wedge, then set aside.

In another small bowl, combine the @vegan ‘Nduja{1/2%sachet} (see ingredients
for amount - add less if you'd prefer things milder) and remaining soured cream
- this is your 'nduja drizzle.

> Vegan 'Nduja has all the spicy, rich flavours of the popular Italian paste -
> but it's completely meat-free! Featuring a hot, umami blend of Calabrian chillies
> and peppers, it has a strong, sweet flavour while carrying 'Nduja's meaty undertones.

Remove the halloumi fries from the cold water, pop them onto a #plate{} lined
with #kitchen paper{} and pat them dry.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high with a drizzle of oil. When hot, fry
the halloumi until golden, turning frequently, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once golden, remove from the heat, drizzle the @honey{15%g} and turn the
halloumi fries to glaze them.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

When everything's ready, transfer the potato fries and pepper slices to your
serving bowls. Top with the glazed halloumi fries.

Top with some avocado and tomato salsa, then spoon over your 'nduja drizzle.

Serve with the slaw, remaining salsa and any remaining lime wedges on the side.

Enjoy!